OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FThe ancient 'Major Oak' tree in
OL,7,FSherwood Forest in Nottinghamshire has
OL,8,Fdied, after its first spring with no
OL,9,Fleaves.
OL,11,FThe tree is thought to be up to 1,200
OL,12,Fyears old, and according to legend it
OL,13,Fsheltered the outlaw Robin Hood, but
OL,14,Fhas been in decline for some years.
OL,16,FThe RSPB, which manages the woodland,
OL,17,Fattributes this to factors including
OL,18,Fhuge numbers of visitors treading on
OL,19,Fthe ground around the tree, and recent
OL,20,Fheatwaves and droughts.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FThe soil around the tree has become
OL,7,Fheavily compacted by millions of
OL,8,Fvisitors, making it harder for rain to
OL,9,Fpenetrate the soil and for the roots
OL,10,Fto take in nutrients. The ground is
OL,11,Fapparently as hard as concrete in some
OL,12,Fparts.
OL,14,FHollie Drake, senior site manager at
OL,15,FRSPB Sherwood Forest, said the tree's
OL,16,Ffailure to produce leaves this year
OL,17,Fwas "heartbreaking for everyone."
OL,26,@yD@EOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FBut she said: "We know the Major Oak
OL,7,Fwill have a lasting legacy, first and
OL,8,Fforemost because it is so inextricably
OL,9,Flinked to Robin Hood and Sherwood
OL,10,FForest.
OL,12,F"But beyond its cultural heritage, the
OL,13,FMajor Oak will continue to provide
OL,14,Fimportant habitat for wildlife,
OL,15,Freminding us why these remarkable
OL,16,Ftrees are so important and why
OL,17,Fprotecting them for the future
OL,18,Fmatters. "
OL,26,@nD@OOUtD@AOUzD@JO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/6
