OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FThe Major Oak won the Woodland Trust's
OL,7,Fannual tree of the year competition in
OL,8,F2014, and was the first to be recorded
OL,9,Fon the charity's ancient tree
OL,10,Finventory ` but the trust said
OL,11,Frecording trees would not "halt their
OL,12,Fcatastrophic decline".
OL,14,FIt has been alive since the Norman
OL,15,Fconquest and continued to grow while
OL,16,Fother Sherwood oaks were used to raise
OL,17,Fthe roof of St Paul's Cathedral, fuel
OL,18,Fthe industrial revolution and build
OL,19,FNelson's navy.
OL,26,@sD@[OUtD@UO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FIts name stuck after the tree was
OL,7,Fmentioned in a book by Major Hayman
OL,8,FRooke in 1790, which started the first
OL,9,Fsignificant waves of tourism to the
OL,10,Fforest, drawing millions over the next
OL,11,Ftwo centuries.
OL,13,FSupports for some of its sprawling
OL,14,Fbranches, in place since the early
OL,15,F20th century, are among the "well-
OL,16,Fintentioned" human interventions that
OL,17,Fare thought to have contributed to its
OL,18,Fdecline.
OL,26,@wD@]OUxD@LO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,349,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F348A1781902064
OL,3,C1,200-year-old oak tree linked to
OL,4,Clegend of Robin Hood has died
OL,6,FFor years, visitors were able to walk
OL,7,Fright up to the tree and even climb
OL,8,Finto its large hollowing trunk, but
OL,9,Fthe area around the tree was fenced in
OL,10,Fthe 1970s, and it has since been
OL,11,Fviewed at a distance.
OL,13,FAcorns and cuttings have been grown
OL,14,Ffrom the tree, and saplings from the
OL,15,Foak have been planted in locations
OL,16,Faround the world, so the tree's legacy
OL,17,Fwill live on.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/6
